cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.IT 

This paper discusses the need for a new routing protocol for ad-hoc edge networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the scalability issues of existing ad-hoc routing protocols, which relates to distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed hash tables (cs.DS). The proposed architecture involves self-certifying cryptographic node identities, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT).
